The important design is that commands and collectors are separate:

- `commands/*` knows how to execute and parse external commands.
- `procfs/*` and `sysfs/*` read Linux files directly.
- `collectors/*` decides which source to use and how to merge fallback data.
- `http/*` only serves already collected data.
- `grpc/*` streams snapshots and accepts sampling config changes.

