## 8. Collection strategy

### 8.1 Static information

Static data should be collected at startup and then refreshed rarely.

Static endpoint:

```text
GET /v1/static
GET /v1/static/os
GET /v1/static/cpu
GET /v1/static/memory
GET /v1/static/disk
GET /v1/static/hardware
```

Static data sources:

| Data | Primary source | Fallback |
|---|---|---|
| OS | `/etc/os-release` | `hostnamectl` |
| Kernel | `uname -a` | `/proc/version` |
| Hostname | `hostname` crate / `/etc/hostname` | `hostnamectl` |
| CPU | `/proc/cpuinfo`, `lscpu` | `/sys/devices/system/cpu` |
| Memory total | `/proc/meminfo` | `free -b` |
| DMI vendor/model | `/sys/class/dmi/id/*` | `hostnamectl`, `lshw` warning allowed |
| Disk inventory | `lsblk -J -b -O` or selected columns | `/sys/block` |
| Disk vendor/model/serial | `/sys/block/*/device/*`, `lsblk` | `lshw -class disk -class storage -json` |
| LVM layout | `lvs/vgs/pvs --reportformat json` | `lsblk` tree |

Do not use `dmidecode` because it usually requires sudo.

Do not require `nvme`. If `/sys/class/nvme` exists, read it directly. If not, report `nvme_cli_available: false`.

### 8.2 Live information

Live data should use `/proc` and `/sys` first.

| Data | Source |
|---|---|
| CPU usage | two reads of `/proc/stat`, compute deltas |
| Load average | `/proc/loadavg` |
| Memory | `/proc/meminfo` |
| Swap | `/proc/meminfo` |
| Disk IO | `/proc/diskstats`, compute rate deltas |
| Mounts | `/proc/self/mountinfo`, `statvfs` if implemented, or `df -P -B1` |
| Top process CPU | `/proc/[pid]/stat` deltas |
| Process memory | `/proc/[pid]/status` or `/proc/[pid]/statm` |
| Process IO | `/proc/[pid]/io`, may be permission-limited |
| Pressure | `/proc/pressure/cpu`, `/proc/pressure/memory`, `/proc/pressure/io` if available |

Use `top -b -n1 -w512` only as an optional fallback or raw endpoint. Do not parse `top` as the primary process collector if `/proc` parsing is available.

## 9. Command catalog

Implement command definitions in `src/commands/catalog.rs`.

Each command must define:

```rust
pub struct CommandSpec {
    pub name: &'static str,
    pub program: &'static str,
    pub args: &'static [&'static str],
    pub timeout_ms: u64,
    pub required: bool,
    pub cache_ttl_seconds: u64,
}
```

Example command catalog:

```rust
pub const LSBLOCK_JSON: CommandSpec = CommandSpec {
    name: "lsblk_json",
    program: "lsblk",
    args: &["-J", "-b", "-o", "NAME,TYPE,SIZE,FSTYPE,MOUNTPOINT,VENDOR,MODEL,SERIAL,ROTA,TRAN"],
    timeout_ms: 2500,
    required: false,
    cache_ttl_seconds: 60,
};

pub const LSCPU: CommandSpec = CommandSpec {
    name: "lscpu",
    program: "lscpu",
    args: &[],
    timeout_ms: 1500,
    required: false,
    cache_ttl_seconds: 3600,
};

pub const TOP_BATCH: CommandSpec = CommandSpec {
    name: "top_batch",
    program: "top",
    args: &["-b", "-n", "1", "-w", "512"],
    timeout_ms: 2500,
    required: false,
    cache_ttl_seconds: 15,
};

pub const LSHW_STORAGE_JSON: CommandSpec = CommandSpec {
    name: "lshw_storage_json",
    program: "lshw",
    args: &["-class", "disk", "-class", "storage", "-json"],
    timeout_ms: 5000,
    required: false,
    cache_ttl_seconds: 3600,
};
```

Important: command failures must not fail the whole endpoint. Return partial data and include command errors in a `warnings` array.

## 10. Command runner requirements

Implement `src/commands/runner.rs`.

Requirements:

1. Use `tokio::process::Command`.
2. Apply timeout with `tokio::time::timeout`.
3. Limit command concurrency using `tokio::sync::Semaphore`.
4. Capture stdout and stderr.
5. Return structured result:

```rust
pub struct CommandOutput {
    pub name: String,
    pub program: String,
    pub args: Vec<String>,
    pub exit_code: Option<i32>,
    pub success: bool,
    pub stdout: String,
    pub stderr: String,
    pub duration_ms: u64,
    pub timed_out: bool,
}
```

6. If the command does not exist, return `success=false` and `error_kind="not_found"`.
7. Never panic on command failure.

